Palmer Penguins: Plot recreation

# start with penguins data frame 
ggplot(data = penguins)

# Map bill depth to the x-axis
ggplot(data = penguins,
mapping = aes(x = bill_depth_mm))

# Map bill length to the y-axis 
ggplot(data = penguins,
 mapping = aes(x = bill_depth_mm,
 y = bill_length_mm))

# Represent each observation with a point 
ggplot(data = penguins,
mapping = aes(x = bill_depth_mm,
y = bill_length_mm)) +
geom_point()

Commonly used features of ggplot that can be mapped to a specific variable in the data are,

color shape size alpha (transparency)

colour, shape, size, alpha (transparency)

Mapping: Determine the size, alpha, etc. of points based on the values of a variable in the data - goes into aes()

Setting: Determine the size, alpha, etc. of points not based on the values of a variable in the data - goes into geom_*() (this was geom_point() in the previous example, but we’ll learn about other geoms soon!)

Mapping vs Setting

# mapping
